fields.description:
The is the only modification I've had to do the the core JIRA api for my customizations. The IssueLinkManager is need to enable my custom condition to pull the inward and outward issue links - my client requested that I enable a workflow which prevents an issue from closing if it is linked (via a particular link type) to another issue.

This is different from SubTasks as a subtask link is only within a project. My users needed the ability to prevent issues in other projects from closing if the problem was a cross-project problem, and there were links between the cross project issues.

I can't find any other requests but I can't think that I'm the only one who will want to have workflow rules based on cross project link types.

Here's the code - my comments not required :)
    // Added 2004.07.25 WAC wcrighton@wacconsulting.com
    // This is needed to enable getting an issue link handle during workflow condition checking
    public IssueLinkManager getIssueLinkManager()
    {
        return (IssueLinkManager) getContainer().getComponentInstanceOfType(IssueLinkManager.class);
    }

