  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4430].
  {panel}

Currently only the Lead of a project or component gets an email on creating new issues. It is not possible to add other persons, so that they too get emails.

It would be great if a project or a component could have watchers similar to single issues.

Another idea is to let the user mark one of his filters, after each issue is created the issue is run through all marked filters, if a filter matches an email report is sent. This would be even more powerful than a "watch project" feature and it would also automatically take of permissions.

